Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 22289df697d919d682a3eb890af6f63c63a30df4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="231606" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2018 20:58:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nathaniel Clark (nclark@whamcloud.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32956&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32956&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2836&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite sanity-quota, subtest test_3&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2836&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2836&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: Re-enable sanity-quota/3,6 for ZFS&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: ec4474bf153b79cb5ac5163f5eec00518ee1a709&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="217104" author="adilger" created="Fri, 22 Dec 2017 10:56:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test is still being skipped for ZFS.  A patch needs to be submitted to remove it from &lt;tt&gt;ALWAYS_EXCEPT&lt;/tt&gt;, with &lt;tt&gt;Test-Parameters: sanity-quota ostfilesystemtype=zfs&lt;/tt&gt; run enough times that we are confident that it is passing consistently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="161848" author="simmonsja" created="Sun, 14 Aug 2016 17:23:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Old blocker for unsupported version&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="95377" author="adilger" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 06:42:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bug was closed, but sanity-quota test_3 and test_6 are still being skipped for ZFS filesystems&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54230" author="pjones" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 05:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53489" author="niu" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 21:20:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This one is for ldiskfs, it&apos;s little bit different with other failures for zfs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53159" author="utopiabound" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2013 23:23:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a slow dd command, which is related other slow dd commands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53053" author="niu" created="Tue, 26 Feb 2013 21:00:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5539&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5539&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53037" author="niu" created="Tue, 26 Feb 2013 04:58:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When approaching quota limit, client turns to sync write (one page by one page), on some slow test system, data flush could take very long time (longer than grace time), then grace could expires before we start testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we&apos;d enlarge the grace time for the test_3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2837&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite sanity-quota, subtest test_6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has the similar problem, we&apos;d enlarge the waiting time for test_6 either.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="52732" author="niu" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 03:55:52 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;14:39:16:running as uid/gid/euid/egid 60000/60000/60000/60000, groups:
14:39:16: [dd] [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;=/dev/zero] [bs=1M] [of=/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity-quota/d3/f.sanity-quota.3-0] [count=1]
14:39:16:1+0 records in
14:39:16:1+0 records out
14:39:16:1048576 bytes (1.0 MB) copied, 0.0296897 s, 35.3 MB/s
14:39:27:Write to exceed soft limit
14:39:27:running as uid/gid/euid/egid 60000/60000/60000/60000, groups:
14:39:27: [dd] [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;=/dev/zero] [of=/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity-quota/d3/f.sanity-quota.3-0] [bs=1K] [count=10] [seek=1024]
14:39:27:10+0 records in
14:39:27:10+0 records out
14:39:27:10240 bytes (10 kB) copied, 9.24401 s, 1.1 kB/s
14:39:28:Disk quotas &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; user quota_usr (uid 60000):
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It used 11 seconds to flush the data, so the grace has expired before the &quot;Writing before timer goes off&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;14:39:30:Write before timer goes off
14:39:30:running as uid/gid/euid/egid 60000/60000/60000/60000, groups:
14:39:30: [dd] [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;=/dev/zero] [of=/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity-quota/d3/f.sanity-quota.3-0] [bs=1K] [count=10] [seek=2048]
14:39:30:dd: writing `/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity-quota/d3/f.sanity-quota.3-0&apos;: Disk quota exceeded
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure why flush 1M bytes data takes so long.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
